What if there's something
dangerous behind that door?

22
00:01:10,980 --> 00:01:15,110
Think, North Star,
before you do anything rash.

23
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:16,490
Very well, very well!

24
00:01:21,830 --> 00:01:25,130
Oh, drat! Let's have a
go at it, shall we?

25
00:01:26,380 --> 00:01:28,240
North Star, please!

26
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:30,420
This could be the Golden Door!

27
00:01:30,420 --> 00:01:32,230
A long long time ago,

28
00:01:32,220 --> 00:01:38,170
the most fearsome creature
ever known terrorized Ponyland.

29
00:01:38,170 --> 00:01:41,920
<i>So, a sorcerer forged
the Golden Door.</i>

30
00:01:41,930 --> 00:01:44,440
<i>A gateway to
the Land of Legends.</i>

31
00:01:44,430 --> 00:01:46,930
<i>A mysterious door of realm.</i>

32
00:01:46,930 --> 00:01:48,900
<i>And it was
through that golden door</i>

33
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:52,150
<i>that the beast was pushed
into the land of legends.</i>

34
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:55,280
<i>As long as no one passes
through the door,</i>

35
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:57,170
<i>the beast will remain there.</i>

36
00:01:57,160 --> 00:02:00,160
So reign in that curiosity
of yours North Star.

37
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:02,610
And stay away from that door!

38
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:04,290
Now, if you'll excuse me.

39
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:06,870
I've had enough
exploring for one day.

40
00:02:09,370 --> 00:02:11,120
A brightfully silly story.

41
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:13,670
I fancy she simply made it up.

42
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:16,440
North Star!

43
00:02:16,430 --> 00:02:20,180
How could anything dangerous
be behind such a lovely door?

44
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:24,800
In any event, Paradise
didn't say not to open it.

45
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,300
She merely said not to pass
through it.

46
00:02:27,310 --> 00:02:29,200
North Star, don't!

47
00:02:31,140 --> 00:02:33,110
Oh, how dreary!

48
00:02:35,150 --> 00:02:38,370
Well, that certainly
was a disappointment.

49
00:02:44,540 --> 00:02:45,490
Ohh!

50
00:02:45,490 --> 00:02:46,820
Stand and deliver!

51
00:02:46,830 --> 00:02:48,500
Oh, no!

52
00:02:48,490 --> 00:02:49,740
Hold steeds.

53
00:02:52,830 --> 00:02:56,800
What manner of pony are these?

54
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,580
Aye, who'd be your master?

55
00:02:58,590 --> 00:03:00,350
Does he have any money?

56
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:04,420
We...we have
no master or money.

57
00:03:04,430 --> 00:03:06,240
No money?

58
00:03:06,230 --> 00:03:12,230
(All cry)

59
00:03:12,850 --> 00:03:15,490
Allow me to introduce myself.

60
00:03:15,490 --> 00:03:17,400
I am Hood, Robin Hood.

61
00:03:17,410 --> 00:03:22,030
And these are my..eh..huh,
merry men.

62
00:03:22,030 --> 00:03:23,040
Merry men?

63
00:03:23,030 --> 00:03:25,280
We are North Star and Lofty.

64
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,160
Welcome to Ponyland!

65
00:03:27,170 --> 00:03:28,370
Ponyland, eh?

66
00:03:28,370 --> 00:03:29,630
Jolly good!

67
00:03:29,620 --> 00:03:32,620
They have a holiday here,
it would make my Merry Men,

68
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:34,450
a bit more merry.

69
00:03:34,460 --> 00:03:35,550
I say everyone-

70
00:03:35,540 --> 00:03:37,510
come out
and have a look.

71
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:43,600
Ahhh!
This is nice.

72
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,050
There's quite a few of you.

73
00:03:45,050 --> 00:03:47,020
You are not all Merry Men.

74
00:03:47,020 --> 00:03:48,270
(Laughs)
No, no.

75
00:03:48,270 --> 00:03:51,350
We're legends and myths.

76
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:54,650
There's Paul Bunyan
and Big, his ox.

77
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:56,230
And Aladdin and his lamp.

78
00:03:56,230 --> 00:03:58,060
And Chaharazad.

79
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:02,570
And there's Hercules.

80
00:04:02,570 --> 00:04:04,230
Uh..Haa! Uhh!

81
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,410
It's coming!
<i>(aligatorsaur roar)</i>

82
00:04:05,410 --> 00:04:07,800
(All gasp)

83
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:09,960
It's coming after us!

84
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:10,990
Close it!

85
00:04:10,990 --> 00:04:11,410
Hurry!

86
00:04:11,410 --> 00:04:12,740
Shut the door!

87
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,420
(All sigh)

88
00:04:14,410 --> 00:04:15,130
I say,

89
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:17,080
what was all that about?

90
00:04:17,080 --> 00:04:20,050
No...no, it's too horrible.

91
00:04:20,050 --> 00:04:21,630
That creature
Paradise mentioned.

92
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:24,100
Could that be
what they're so afraid of,

93
00:04:24,090 --> 00:04:26,560
that they all have
come to Ponyland?

94
00:04:31,430 --> 00:04:32,730
Quite.

95
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:36,480
Hmm, I guess
we should let everyone know.

96
00:04:36,490 --> 00:04:39,280
(tremoring)

97
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:45,270
Ohhh...

98
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,870
Oh darling, Paradise!

99
00:04:47,860 --> 00:04:50,360
Such a lovely bouquet.

100
00:04:50,370 --> 00:04:52,210
I would give
it to my true love,

101
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,780
but, where is he?

102
00:04:53,790 --> 00:04:56,380
Will he never come
into my life?

103
00:04:56,370 --> 00:04:59,120
Oh, Heart Throb, don't be
discouraged.

104
00:04:59,130 --> 00:05:01,020
Your true love will show up.

105
00:05:01,010 --> 00:05:03,510
He's out there,
I'm sure of it.

