♪ A royal highness ♪

110
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:23,700
♪ But your Romeo will
show up in the end ♪

111
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:27,900
♪ But when will he arrive? ♪

112
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:31,240
♪ How long must I wait? ♪

113
00:05:32,580 --> 00:05:36,340
♪ I know it will be soon ♪

114
00:05:36,330 --> 00:05:40,210
♪ But let's leave the date
to fate ♪

115
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:45,140
♪ There's a prince in your
future Heart Throb ♪

116
00:05:45,140 --> 00:05:49,480
♪ And he'll be exactly who
you're dreaming of ♪

117
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:51,770
♪ Handsome and disarming ♪

118
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:53,980
♪ A regular prince
charming ♪

119
00:05:53,980 --> 00:05:57,730
♪ When he comes you'll know
at once it's love ♪

120
00:05:57,730 --> 00:05:59,900
♪ Yes, when he comes ♪

121
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:06,160
♪ you'll know
at once it's love ♪

122
00:06:08,860 --> 00:06:11,080
You called?

123
00:06:15,030 --> 00:06:19,540
My darling! Where have
you been all my life?

124
00:06:19,540 --> 00:06:21,950
(Shy)
Oh! Nowhere special, heh.

125
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:25,100
Ah, who...who are you?

126
00:06:25,090 --> 00:06:27,790
Well, Prince Charming of course.

127
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:31,110
And I've been searching
my whole life through

128
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,350
for you, my sweet.

129
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:33,430
You have?

130
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:37,030
Promise me
we'll be together always?

131
00:06:37,020 --> 00:06:39,190
Darling, you needn't even ask.

132
00:06:41,060 --> 00:06:42,310
Huh?

133
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:43,480
Dearest!

134
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:47,560
Oh, how I've longed
to find one so fair as you.

135
00:06:47,570 --> 00:06:50,630
But, but what about Heart Throb?

136
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:51,570
Forget the past!

137
00:06:51,570 --> 00:06:53,540
Think only of the present.

138
00:06:53,540 --> 00:06:56,660
Us, together.
Now and always.

139
00:06:57,910 --> 00:06:59,790
Ohh, my one true love.

140
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:05,410
Oh, my sweet!
How can you pass me by?

141
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:10,250
True Heart, it's you I love!

142
00:07:10,890 --> 00:07:13,140
Darling, Don't go.

143
00:07:13,140 --> 00:07:15,930
I've got a funny
feeling about this.

144
00:07:21,430 --> 00:07:23,930
(groaning)
Rrrraaaahhh!

145
00:07:28,410 --> 00:07:32,670
There! I just love a
tidy place, don't you?

146
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:35,440
Oh, yes, Hercules,
so do we!

147
00:07:35,450 --> 00:07:36,540
I haven't had so much fun

148
00:07:36,530 --> 00:07:40,000
since I cleaned
the Agean's stables

149
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,870
Filthy dirt. filthy,
filthy, filthy...

150
00:07:49,130 --> 00:07:52,350
Just like
a willow in the breeze.

151
00:07:52,350 --> 00:07:54,100
(All giggle)

152
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:56,380
That's it my little ones.

153
00:07:58,890 --> 00:08:02,780
And that's how we do the dance
of the seven waves.

154
00:08:08,450 --> 00:08:09,740
Gee-Wiz!

155
00:08:09,730 --> 00:08:12,310
It's a wonderful day
for a picnic, Lickety-Split.

156
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,580
It truly is.

157
00:08:13,570 --> 00:08:16,490
Those clouds have me worried
Buttons--

158
00:08:16,490 --> 00:08:19,710
'Cause it looks like
it's gonna rain, and I might

159
00:08:19,710 --> 00:08:21,410
What's that?

160
00:08:21,410 --> 00:08:23,660
It's a lamp that
Aladdin fellow traded to me.

161
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:25,540
It should clean right up.

162
00:08:25,550 --> 00:08:27,590
I think he tricked you,
Buttons,

163
00:08:27,580 --> 00:08:30,080
there's no place
to put a light bulb.

164
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:32,640
(both gasp in amazement)

165
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:34,420
I am the Genie of the Lamp

166
00:08:34,420 --> 00:08:36,390
and I'm obliged to grant
you three wishes.

167
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:38,670
May I take your order, please?

168
00:08:38,680 --> 00:08:41,270
You go first, Lickety-Split.

169
00:08:41,260 --> 00:08:43,760
I wish the weather was perfect.

170
00:08:43,770 --> 00:08:45,410
Perfect! Hmm..

171
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:47,820
Could you be more specific?
Temperature?

172
00:08:47,820 --> 00:08:49,270
Well...

173
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:52,410
Eighty two, sixty four,
a hundred and seventy nine?

174
00:08:52,410 --> 00:08:53,610
Uh, eighty two?

175
00:08:53,610 --> 00:08:55,740
Relative humidity?

176
00:08:55,750 --> 00:09:00,120
C'mon c'mon! What'll it be?
Five percent, ten, ninety?

177
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:01,210
Whub-ah,
I haven't thought of it.

178
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:04,120
And I'll also need to know
the prevailing wind speed

179
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:07,250
and the percentage of
the color orange in the sunset.

180
00:09:07,260 --> 00:09:09,520
Look all I want
is a perfect day,

181
00:09:09,510 --> 00:09:12,010
So what's so difficult
about that?

182
00:09:12,010 --> 00:09:13,460
And what about the sky?

183
00:09:13,460 --> 00:09:16,680
You have your cerulean blue,
your robin's egg blue,

184
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:21,470
your royal blue or
blueberry blue, cobalt blue?

185
00:09:28,060 --> 00:09:29,230
(Lofty)
Well, North Star,

186
00:09:29,230 --> 00:09:32,780
I hope you're satisfied
opening that door.

187
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:35,360
We're practically being crowded
out of the estate

188
00:09:35,370 --> 00:09:37,910
by uninvited guests.

189
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,790
Shame on you!

190
00:09:39,790 --> 00:09:41,040
Come, come, Lofty!

191
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,910
'Tisn't that bad.

192
00:09:42,910 --> 00:09:43,540
No?

193
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:44,740
What about the legend?

194
00:09:44,740 --> 00:09:47,710
If anyone passes
through that door?

195
00:09:47,710 --> 00:09:50,250
Everyone came through the
door already.

196
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:54,000
And we shut it behind us,
there was no monster.

197
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,380
Monster?

198
00:09:55,390 --> 00:09:57,480
(panicked shouts)

199
00:09:57,470 --> 00:09:59,140
We don't
have to worry.

200
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:02,890
Oh?
Then why are they so nervous?

201
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:06,020
(Heart Throb)
Prince Charming, darling?

202
00:10:10,350 --> 00:10:12,940
How romantic?

203
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:18,770
(roars)

204
